.TH mlib_SignalLinear2ADPCM4Bits 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_SignalLinear2ADPCM4Bits \- adaptive differential pulse code modulation
(ADPCM)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_SignalLinear2ADPCM4Bits\fR(\fBmlib_u8 *\fR\fIadpcm\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_s16 *\fR\fIpcm\fR, \fBvoid *\fR\fIstate\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIn\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_SignalLinear2ADPCM4Bits()\fR function performs adaptive
differential pulse code modulation (ADPCM) in compliance with the ITU
(former CCITT) G.721, G.723, and G.726 specifications. It converts data from
16-bit linear PCM to G.721 or G.726 32kbps 4-bit ADPCM format.
.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIadpcm\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
ADPCM code array.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIpcm\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Linear PCM sample array.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIstate\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Internal structure of the codec.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIn\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 9n
.rt
Number of samples in the source array.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns
\fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
